        "id": 9173
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-01T13:26:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "A single Update can carry both, but I kept them separate on purpose: sending withdraw-then-advertise guarantees the peer drops the old NLRI before installing the new one, and RFC 4271 https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc4271#section-4.3 says the same prefix SHOULD NOT appear in both the Withdrawn and NLRI fields of one Update, which is exactly what a same-prefix/different-label change would produce here. Since this is a rare replace path, I favored correct ordering over saving one message",
      "parentUuid": "2ba7f5dc_aa1fa7b5",
      "revId": "9304e15ff89b2c1dc48ce41df427470116d132ec",
      "serverId": "7fc14799-209e-464c-9743-7a06c2c21a81"
